 to the light-shielding layer is greater than 0 and less than nF&#x394;, where n is the refractive index at the focal position of the micro lens, F is the aperture value of the micro lens, and &#x394; is the diffraction limit of the micro lens. This enables variation in the pupil intensity distribution of the pixel for focusing due to positional production tolerance of components to be suppressed.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>